      "content": "I am so sorry you are feeling this heavy weight of self-blame, but imagining that they would be happier without you is a painful thought that usually comes from exhaustion, not truth. Your very presence—being there even when you are struggling—is often a profound form of love that helps them identify with your humanity rather than perfecting a fictional version of a parent. Please take this moment to call your support system or a therapist immediately so you can find the perspective you need to lift this dark feeling.",
